			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Establishing a beach head...<a name="55955"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 10 04 5:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I read alot about people using proximity agro.  I use this as much as possible, but perhaps I am unlucky.  I always get at least one room where I have a mob hiding on both sides of a doorway, out of LoS, and one standing a little further in, then one on each side of the one further in.  I cant get into proximty agro of the ones hiding on each side of the doorway without getting in agro range of the one slightly in the room.  Once I agro the one a little bit in I get a 5 mob pull.  If I cast on any of them its a 5 mob pull.  Its a real pain when this is the first room and there is no space between me and my group.  If some of those mobs are casters then I get nuked while trying to fade with almost no space between me and my group.
<br />

<br />
I have had a number of deaths from this set-up, but here is what I have done that seems to help the initial break:
<br />

<br />
have party invis
<br />
tag one non casting mob with snare
<br />
run to zone out, and zone out
<br />
party tags snared mob
<br />
immediately zone back in
<br />
start mezing if there are adds 
<br />

<br />
I can get to zone out with only 2-3 mobs leaving the pull room.  If you are a real slow zoner this won't work.
<br />

<br />
This set-up is just evil.  Mistmoore is where I see this, and have actually had it where there are multiple visible mobs on both sides at zone in.  
<br />

<br />
Racket says; &quot;Ok guys we are going to have to establish a beach head&quot;
<br />

<br />
Warrior says; &quot;What the h*ll are you talking about?&quot;
<br />

<br />
about lul...
<br />

<br />
Some people really hate it.  I use it, and I like it.  I would like it more if it didnt resist so much.  Its a great pulling tool though.  You dont need line of sight and its got good range, lul a mob, if it sticks, great next target, if you get a resist try again and if you get an agro resist then you get a bunch of mobs and just have to sort like normal.
<br />

<br />
Use the resists, they can have a function.
<br />

<br />
rack
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
